article.headline: New Hampshire 64, Brown 61
article.story: DURHAM, NH -- Tyrece Gibbs and Radar Onguetou hit key 3-pointers in the final minutes and New Hampshire came from 14 points behind to beat Brown, 64-61, Saturday in a non-conference game. Gibbs, who led the Wildcats (3-3) with 19 points, hit the last of his five treys with just under 5 minutes to play to break a 54-all tie. After a pair of Brown free throws, Gibbs' no-look pass hit a wide open Onguetou, who scored. After two more free throws pulled Brown (3-5) within 59-58, Onguetous, who had 9 points, drilled a 3-pointer with 1:36 left. With the score 64-61, Brown, of the Ivy League, had one more chance, but Peter Sullivan missed a 3-point try with four seconds left and Alvin Abreu grabbed the rebound for the Wildcats. Matt Mullery, whose 3-pointer put Brown ahead 54-51, led the Bears with 15 points.
